Personally, i think these two stories goes to show, sometimes it just takes a rather harsh diciplining to correct something. Believe it or not ghandi, sometimes violence is the answer. to the posters attacking rahdar you are just as bad, violently attacking him with words, and from my experience words hurt far worse than fists, i still haven't over come the social stigma that boy had inflicted on me, but his nose is fine, you can't even tell...but anyone around me knows i still have problems with just the words he has said, which over time, go really deep into a persons heart and soul...So congrats radahr for teaching that man a lesson, hopefully he doesn't continue his rudish, and obnoxious behavior. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usneakstershenanigans.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sneakster Shenanigans</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/dagger.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/02 11:08:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8767.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: what good?</span><hr size=1> Thank Jebus for people like Mythas /roll eyes<br>
<br>
Don't tell me the few people disagreeing with Radahr are 'violently hurting him with words'.  Nothing has been said to violently insult him.  I really find nothing heroic about you sucker-slamming some kid and then punching his older brother in the face for trying to defend him.  In my opinion just turning the other cheek would have made you the bigger man.  Fight violence with violence, don't fight words (or horns) with violence.<br>
<br>
And I seriously doubt that you breaking some guy's nose made them outstanding citizens.  More like them just growing up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umythasgrimlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mythas Grimlore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/02 1:18:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8767.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> i got tired</span><hr size=1> Yeah, i know turning the other way makes me a bigger man. However, its constantly turning the other cheek, for months on end, thats when it gets to me. It enraged me so much that nothing was being done to lots of other people like me, where they turn the other cheek...e.g ( kinda the same )<br>
<br>
