<br>
I know said example is a little out of context, but it all boils down to the same thing, its easy to say when its not you. And if it is you, and it makes you hurt, then stand up for yourself because no one is better than anyone else, and no one deserves to be treated like that. I got tired of being pushed down, over and over and over agian. After a while, those things that he said really began to sink in, it seemed his whole existance was to make mine horrid. So, one day, i stood up for my self. Don't get me wrong i tried to get him to stop before * appologies for not putting that in the story * but yes i verbally asked him to stop many a time. It seemed everytime i asked him to stop he only did it more...<br>
<br>
Maybe some people are too meek to stand up for themselves, thats fine. Maybe some people have the strenght, steadfastness * not a word but you get the idea *, and faith of job, but i don't. I prefer to stand for my self, and i just got tired of turning the other cheek, i got tired of going home and telling my self those things aren't true, and having it not work...I got tired of dreading every day of school...So i decided to rid my self of my problems. <br>
<br>
Roll your eyes all you want, turn your other cheek, i just hope you have something in your life that makes you miserable day in and day out, and see what you do. If you are the kind of person that can just let it roll off your shoulder then kudos to you. However, if you can't i'd like to see what you could do...Could you save your family if need be, or would you just let what ever was happening happen??? Its always easy to say to do something until it happens to you...<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usneakstershenanigans.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sneakster Shenanigans</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/dagger.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/02 1:41:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8767.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i got tired</span><hr size=1> Fighting violence with violence is one thing.  If he had hit you first, then there really wouldn't be a problem.  Its when you let the words get to you and strike back with violence that you have done wrong.  I would much rather fight words with words.  Say that day he'd chewed you out bad, so you punched him.  The next week he cornered you with a bat and hit you in the head.  Next week you brought a knife and shanked him.  Maybe he'd die, maybe he'd live.  Next him or his brother shoots you.  All because he said some stuff that wasn't true.  Maybe you were justified, maybe you weren't.  Its hard to say what I would do if I was in a similar position.  I think you (Mythas) were more justified in what you did that Radahr.  <br>
<br>
In the end, violence doesn't make people better people.  If got some bully of your back, which is cool.  But it could have ended differently. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uragwheed.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ragwheed</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/02 2:37:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8767.topic&index=32>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://wombat.homestead.com/files/2Daa.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i got tired</span><hr size=1> Moral of the story?  Congrats, you now have a criminal record, which companies look at when you apply for a job. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usangdraax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sang Draax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/02 11:13:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8767.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i got tired</span><hr size=1> It's all perspective really.<br>
